<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hello, the use-package documentation says that when any of the following keywords are used: <code>:commands, :bind, :bind*, :bind-keymap, :bind-keymap*, :mode, :interpreter, or :hook</code> the packages get deferred automatically.</p> <p>I have <code>corfu</code> and <code>cape</code> and none of them contain any of those keywords:</p> <pre><code> (use-package corfu :init (global-corfu-mode) :custom (corfu-auto t) (corfu-cycle t) (corfu-auto-prefix 1) (corfu-auto-delay 0.1) (corfu-quit-no-match &#39;separator) (corfu-excluded-modes &#39;(org-mode mu4e-compose-mode))) (use-package cape :init (add-to-list &#39;completion-at-point-functions #&#39;cape-dabbrev) (add-to-list &#39;completion-at-point-functions #&#39;cape-file)) </code></pre> <p>I don&#39;t think <code>corfu</code> is something I need right when Emacs starts up so I think it is safe to defer both <code>corfu</code> and <code>cape</code> manually with <code>:defer t</code> right?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/zoliky"> /u/zoliky </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wo55gw/defer_loading_of_corfu_with_usepackage/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wo55gw/defer_loading_of_corfu_with_usepackage/">[comments]</a></span>